szakacs.kpi.fei.tuke.intrfc

Interface PlayerToken


  • public interface PlayerToken
    The interface for a token that is unique for each player and which serves as an authentication of sorts to prevent other players in multiplayer scenarios from interfering with one another unduly.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean validate(PlayerToken token)
      A method which check if the token passed to it is valid (it basically checks if it is the same instance).

    • Method Detail

      • validate

        boolean validate(PlayerToken token)
        A method which check if the token passed to it is valid (it basically checks if it is the same instance).
        Parameters:
        token - the token passed to the method in which validate() is called and which needs to be checked.
        Returns:
        boolean true if token is valid | false otherwise
